# Machine-only Gradle JVM (do not merge into committed nutonic/gradle.properties).
#
# Gradle reads org.gradle.java.home from (among others):
#   1) Project gradle.properties  → keep shared; do not commit paths here.
#   2) User gradle.properties     → recommended for a fixed JDK path.
#   3) JAVA_HOME                  → recommended for teams (CI-friendly).
#
# If the daemon must use a specific JDK but PATH still picks an older java first, add ONE line
# to your user file (create the file if needed):
#   Windows:  %USERPROFILE%\.gradle\gradle.properties
#   macOS/Linux: ~/.gradle/gradle.properties
#
# Use forward slashes on Windows. Example:
# org.gradle.java.home=C:/Program Files/Eclipse Adoptium/jdk-21.0.9.10-hotspot
#
# This repo gitignores `gradle.properties.PERSONAL`. Gradle does not load that filename by
# default. To apply the same settings, copy the `org.gradle.java.home` line (uncommented) into:
#   %USERPROFILE%\.gradle\gradle.properties   (Windows)
#   ~/.gradle/gradle.properties               (macOS / Linux)
# Or set JAVA_HOME to a JDK 17+ and ensure `java`/`javac` on PATH come from that JDK.
